				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Anyone boxing a Bard and Cleric?<a name="69892"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 17 04 5:00 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Better get RS5 on the cleric, because its going to take agro alot.
<br />

<br />
If they are mezzable you could use the cleric to reduce the time you mez/heal while meleeing, but after mez the mob will take off after the cleric more often then not.
<br />

<br />
Now if you don't mind the cleric dieing, you could use it to help you take a mob that you can almost take solo, heal yourself half way thru and sacrifice the cleric.
<br />

<br />
Basically, a bard has no tools to generate agro in the modern EQ.  Even spells like slow don't have the impact on us as they do other high-agro classes, otherwise after I've refreshed slow on a mob for the 4th time it would be on me and nothing could take it off.
<br />

<br />
Sony doesn't support 2-boxing on a single computer, but many people still manage, I figure by using a 3rd party program to manage the windows, and turning sound off as well as setting the graphics as low as they go.  The framelimiter should help a lot as well.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">- I used to drive the short bus for a living.  Growing up on the internet leaves me uniquely qualified to handle retards at high speeds.</span></td>
