			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Anyone boxing a Bard and Cleric?<a name="69894"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 17 04 5:04 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">My question for anyone who does this is, is it possible to keep agro off the Cleric when he heals you? In the case of chant kiting it seems unlikely since the agro nerf.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I agree.
<br />

<br />
With some hate/anger weapons and some decent DEX and Weapon Affinity AA, though, it might be a very decent combo (with bard meleeing) assuming you had some good hotkeys set up on the cleric box.  You may have to heal the bard a LOT though because of the bard's lower than average melee DPS (longer fight) and also lower than average (incoming) damage mitigation.
<br />

<br />
If you attempt to 2-box ANYTHING with a bard, though, make the second toon as low-maintenance as possible.  Good hotkeys on the second toon are a MUST.
<br />

<br />
Quite honestly, I've two-boxed several different combos since I started several years back, and I just can't seem to get the knack for doing it with my bard.  Bard's demand very nearly ALL your attention if played well enough.  I really wouldn't have it any other way though.  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
