				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Anyone boxing a Bard and Cleric?<a name="69896"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 17 04 5:07 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I started 2 boxing with a shaman as my second on the same computer.  I chose shaman because of their utility factor and considerable heals.  I figured if I absolutely needed a cleric healing then my bard was pbly not capable of tanking whatever the mob was.  Aggro was tough to hold when slows got resisted but keep hacking away and keep toropr/quiessence passed out and all is well.  The bard/shaman combo was one I was happy with for a long time.  If my warrior was not on the same account as shaman i would probably still play her.
<br />

<br />
http://www.lavishsoft.com
<br />

<br />
All the information you could ever want for playing 2 instances of EQ on the same computer well can be found at that site.  They are the makers of the windowing program called WinEQ which is far superior to EQWindows in my opinion.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Edit:  If you cant maintain aggro through dps/procs/songs then a Blade of Carnage is not a bad weapon to consider.  It is a good ratio, good stats and good hate.  Or an Force of Ykesha proc on a solid dps weapon is my solution.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
