			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Anyone boxing a Bard and Cleric?<a name="69932"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 18 04 10:07 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've been 2boxing a cleric and a bard for over a year now, and I really enjoy it. I don't find aggro to ever be a serious problem, but I have a solid routine down and I rarely stray from it. I really suggest using HoTs like others have also said, it might cost a bit more mana in the long run but it really saves you a lot of worrying. I do all my 2boxing straight melee, usually with the cleric meleeing too because my dps is so pathetic. Here are a few tips from my experiences:
<br />

<br />
-Pull with as much aggro as possible. Ex: Use dispell for the initial aggro, then HoS, then slow, so by the time the mob reaches you, the aggro is well established. 
<br />

<br />
-It's all in the routine. I can't stress this enough, if you develop something repeatable and then tweak your hotkeys based on that process, you'll find it much much smoother. No scrambling, just a smooth ride. My routine goes something like this:
<br />
Pull as mentioned above, engage melee once I reach camp and end twist leaving slow song on (or mana depending on situation). 
<br />
Tap cleric hotkeys for assist, damage shield and hammer pet. 
<br />
HoT and move cleric into melee, or just plop down and med if needed. 
<br />
Continue twist and melee with bard. 
<br />
This seems to work great for me, there's always a temporary gap in my twist but I leave the most important song on while performing cleric functions, then I pick the bard twist up asap. After a lot of practice I can hammer the cleric functions out before my whole twist fades, thanks to a solid routine.
<br />

<br />
-Make the last line in all of your cleric's hotkeys /sit. This is a minor thing and may seem like common sense, but every corner you can cut will help tremendously. 
<br />

<br />
-Try to limit the use of straight heals to in between fights. One HoT during and one CH in between mobs is what I try to stay to, even if I'm at 5% when the fight is over, I save a ton of mana. 
<br />

<br />
-Keep a stun memmed at all times with your cleric, it can save you much more effectively than root, in my experiences anyway. 
<br />

<br />
-Make some convenient targetting hotkeys for your cleric, this is very important, nothing can piss you off quite like dying because you clicked on your bard 50 times and couldn't target. Avoid using the mouse all together, setup a system for yourself that is quicker and more accurate than that, keep it all to one side of the keyboard, or get a nostromo. Speed saves lives, this is an important truth. I use the toggle last two targets button a ton. 
<br />

<br />
-Travelling can be a real pain in the a$, especially if your second computer is made of old spare parts like mine and your new one is a powerhouse. Believe it or not, I take my cleric seperate from my bard as much as I can, and it's actually easier in most cases (depending on where I go of course). Avoid PoK, the lag will have you banging your head against the wall trying to keep your duo together. When it's necessary, I have the cleric look down on autofollow while I use an exterior camera view with my bard on my fast comp to keep track. Even then, I barely use bard speed. 
<br />

<br />
-As tempting as it is, don't take people you don't know on. If you do, make <u>d*mn sure</u> you explain the fact that you're boxing, you don't have to take others into your group, once you do it's your responsibility to keep them alive, don't be a bonehead. 
<br />

<br />
Anyways that's all I can think of for now, stuff I wish someone had told me when I started 2boxing blind. Just be cautious till your skill catches up with you and try to start doing this in secluded areas/dungeons. I learned everything in Droga/Nurga as well as Chardok and Veksar, which btw is a great place to duo if your cleric has lots of mana, those undead dots kick a$. 
<br />

<br />
Best of luck and be safe!
<br />

<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
