			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Anyone boxing a Bard and Cleric?<a name="69945"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 18 04 11:44 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I box a 65 shaman with my bard, mainly because it used to be old main so I had him handy.  I find that 3 chants, Trusik and Marr (from GtW click) is enough to hold agro and still dish out decent DPS.  I can stick shaman slow once the mob gets to about 92%.  This frees up me to not twist slow.  Additionally, with shaman slow, extended buff HoT's, and focused direct heals, I can take on some pretty beefy mobs.  
<br />

<br />
The trick to this boxing is always pull singles.  More than one and it will mess up agro and your routine.  If you get a single mob, bring it into camp slowed and HoS'd, beat on it quick to get the shaman slow in before HoS drops. From there, it is just hotkeys to HoT, nuke/dot as needed.
<br />

<br />
What the shaman gives over a cleric is the superior slow, way fast mana regen, and better DPS.  The cleric gives rezzes and better buffs.  
<br />
</span></td>
